    {
      "text": "Which of the following is a permanent social group?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Herd"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Mob"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Band"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Crowd"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 2,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Answer: C) Band</strong></p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>Explanation:</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Group </strong>refers to several people that are located gathered or classed together.  In sociological terms, groups can fundamentally be distinguished from one another by the extent to which their nature influences individuals and how.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Types of social groups:</strong></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" data-author=\"NA\" data-hash=\"\" data-license=\"NA\" data-source=\"NA\" data-tags=\"\" height=\"788\" src=\"https://image.prepladder.com/content/Jjl8zqLFVYeOpTK4lTgA1734074850.png\" width=\"830\" /></p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p> </p>",
