    {
      "text": "Which of the following best describes a joint family?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "A Family with husband, wife and biological/adopted children."
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "A family with Grandparents, parents and children."
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "A family with Grandparents, parents and children living along with uncle, aunt and their families."
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "A family with both parents are not together."
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 2,
      "solution": "<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>Answer: C) A family with Grandparents, parents and children living along with uncle, aunt and their families</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Explanation:</strong></p>\n\n<p>A family is a biological, social, and cultural unit consisting of people who are biologically related and share a common kitchen. </p>\n\n<p>A <strong>Joint family</strong> usually consists of  Grandparents, parents, and children along with uncles, aunts, and their families.</p>\n\n<p>Other important requirements for a joint family include:</p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>\n\t<p>Males related by blood</p>\n\t</li>\n\t<li>\n\t<p>Common pool of income</p>\n\t</li>\n\t<li>\n\t<p>Common kitchen</p>\n\t</li>\n\t<li>\n\t<p>Common property</p>\n\t</li>\n\t<li>\n\t<p>Authority vested in senior most of the family usually</p>\n\t</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Types of families:</strong></p>\n\n<table align=\"center\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:659px\">\n\t<tbody>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Type of family</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>People in the family</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Nuclear family </strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\">Father, mother and children (Option A)</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>New family</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\">A family <10 years old</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Joint family</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\">Grandparents, parents, children along with uncle, aunt and their family (Option C)</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Three generation family</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\">Grandparents, parents, children (Option B)</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Broken family</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\">Either of the parents has died, or the couple is divorced/separated (Option D)</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Problem family</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\">Family lagging behind the rest of the community</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Communal family</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\">A group of families or single people who live and work together sharing possessions and responsibilities</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Dysfunctional family</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align:center\">A family where abuse/conflict is common for individuals, and the rest of the family is okay with it.</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>",
