      "correct_choice_id": 0,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Answer: A) Upper Class</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Explanation:</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Modified Kuppuswamy scale:</strong></p>\n\n<table align=\"center\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:628px\">\n\t<tbody>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Purpose</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\">To assess the socio-economic status (SES) of urban families in India.</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Components</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\">1. Education of the head of the family.</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\">2. Occupation of the head of the family.</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\">3. Monthly family income.</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Education Score</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Illiterate: 1</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Primary school: 2</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Middle school: 3</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\">High school: 4</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Intermediate/Post high school diploma: 5 Graduate/Postgraduate: 6</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Profession or Honors: 7</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Occupation Score</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Unemployed: 1</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Unskilled worker: 2</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Semi-skilled worker: 3</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Skilled worker: 4</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Clerical, Shop-owner, Farmer: 5</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Semi-professional: 6</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Professional: 10</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Income Score </strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\">The family income per month in Rs.</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\">The income scale has been recalculated using India's average consumer price index for Industrial workers for the year 2021.</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\"> </p>\n\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><100: 1</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\">101-299: 2</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\">300-499: 3</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\">500-749: 4</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\">750-999: 6</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\">1000-1999: 10</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\">=2000: 12</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>SES Classification</strong></p>\n\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\">(Option B, C and D)</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Upper Class: 26-29</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Upper Middle Class: 16-25</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Lower Middle Class: 11-15</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Upper Lower Class: 5-10</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Lower Class: <5</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p>Based on Mr. Sharms’s components:</p>\n\n<p>Education: 7 points</p>\n\n<p>Occupation: 10 points</p>\n\n<p>Monthly Family Income: 12 points</p>\n\n<p><strong>Total Score: 7 + 10 + 12 = 29 points</strong></p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p> </p>",
