    {
      "text": "A family living in rural India. They struggle to make ends meet, and their diet consists mainly of rice and lentils. They lack access to proper sanitation and healthcare. The family's income is inconsistent and often falls short of covering their basic needs. Based on the scenario, this family would most likely be classified as:",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Above Poverty Line"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Below Poverty Line"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Upper Middle Class"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Middle Class"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 1,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Answer: B) Below Poverty Line</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Explanation:</strong></p>\n\n<p>Below Poverty Line (BPL) is defined based on criteria like insufficient <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5f526a682c16927771831cac5b3711\">calorie</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"6cdcd39cf2169277719068e247e38d\">intake</span> and low per <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"ea701c975f169277718359559b503c\">capita</span> income. While the scenario doesn't provide exact numbers, the family's struggles clearly align with these criteria.</p>\n\n<p>The scenario describes a family <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"c4e40f33721692777202dd7486f4f4\">facing</span> hardships indicative of poverty:</p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li><strong>Poor Diet:</strong> A diet primarily of rice and lentils suggests limited nutritional variety, which is common in poverty.</li>\n\t<li><strong>Lack of Sanitation and Healthcare:</strong> These are significant indicators of low living standards often associated with poverty.</li>\n\t<li><strong>Inconsistent Income:</strong> An inability to consistently afford basic needs is a strong characteristic of being below the poverty line.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>Criteria of BPL:</strong></p>\n\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:728px\">\n\t<tbody>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td rowspan=\"3\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>According to Tendulkar committee</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\"> </td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Rural areas </strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Urban areas</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Per <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"ea701c975f169277718359559b503c\">capita</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5f526a682c16927771831cac5b3711\">calorie</span> intake</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><2400 <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"bf7703756016927771905a4e6a2823\">kcal</span> per day</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><2100 <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"bf7703756016927771905a4e6a2823\">kcal</span> per day</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Per <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"ea701c975f169277718359559b503c\">capita</span> Income</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><27/- INR per day</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><33/- INR per day</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>According to Rangarajan committee</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td colspan=\"3\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Per <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"ea701c975f169277718359559b503c\">capita</span> income is <32/- INR per day in the rural area.</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li><47/- INR per day in the urban area.</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>As per World Bank</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td colspan=\"3\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>If the per <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"ea701c975f169277718359559b503c\">capita</span> income is <2.15 US $ per day, this is an extreme poverty level.</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>Option A: </strong>This contradicts the scenario, as APL households typically can afford basic needs and have a better standard of living.</p>\n\n<p><strong>Options C and D: </strong>The family's struggles with basic needs rule out these possibilities.</p>\n\n<p> </p>",
